            "Fake plainclothes police wallet check: Scammers approach tourists claiming there are counterfeit notes in circulation and ask to inspect your wallet or cash, then steal money or cards. Real Belgian police will never ask to see or take your money on the street - insist on going to the nearest police station or call 101.",
            "Spill and distraction theft: Someone 'accidentally' spills a drink, ice cream, or sauce on you, then helps clean it while an accomplice steals your wallet or phone. Another version involves offering a free bracelet, flower, or help with something. Politely decline and walk away immediately.",
            "Chocolate shop weight & swap trick: Some shops near tourist areas show attractive displays but deliver lower quality or less weight than advertised, or swap premium boxes for cheaper ones after payment. Buy chocolate from well-known, reputable shops with clear pricing.",
